  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cholera Prevention and Response through Oxfam</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of the project to contribute to the reduction in the annual incidence of cholera from 3% to 0.5% of affected communities in the North and Northeast departments by June 2015. This goal will be achieved through improving the capacities of HRC and governmental institutions to respond to and prevent cholera and reducing the target population&#x2019;s vulnerability to cholera. The key activities of the project are: 

Facilitate the inclusion of HRC in cholera response activities through coordination and cluster meetings with key WASH/health actors.

Training of 210 HRC team members (team leaders and volunteers) in cholera prevention and response.

Construction and rehabilitation of 5 water and sanitation facilities in health centers treating cholera patients.

Rehabilitation of 7 priority water systems, including the creation and revitalization of CAEPA/CPEs.

Implementation of mass media activities to promote safe sanitation, appropriate domestic water management, correct hygiene practices and food handling.</narrative>
  </description>
